<script async>window.wf_pixel_generic_signifyd = (data) => {
  // if store_id is missing
  if (!data.store_id) {
    return;
  }

  const generateRandomGuid = () => {
    return 'xxxxxxxx-xxxx-4xxx-yxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx'
    .replace(/[xy]/g, function (c) {
        const r = Math.random() * 16 | 0,
            v = c == 'x' ? r : (r & 0x3 | 0x8);
        return v.toString(16);
    });
  }

  /**
   * This function retrieves a cookie if it exists.
   *
   * @param {String} key cookie name being fetched
   *
   * @returns cookie value
   */
  const getCookie = (key) => {
    const cookieEntry = document.cookie.split(';').find(attribute => {
      return attribute.trim().startsWith(key + '=');
    });

    return cookieEntry ? cookieEntry.split('=')[1] : null;
  }

  /**
   * This function saves a cookie with a explicit expiration time. Returns true on success.
   *
   * @param {String} cookieKey              cookie name
   * @param {String} cookieValue            cookie value
   * @param {Number} expirationMilliseconds expiration time in milliseconds
   * @param {Object} attributes             cookie attributes map
   *
   * @returns boolean true if cookie was succesfully saved.
   */
  const setCookie = (cookieKey, cookieValue, expirationMilliseconds, attributes = {}) => {
    // reject calls without key, value, or expiration time
    if (!cookieKey || !expirationMilliseconds) {
      return false
    }

    // convert attributes into cookie attributes
    const cookieAttributes = Object.entries(attributes).reduce((attributesArray, [attributeKey, attributeValue]) => {
      if (attributeValue !== null) {
        attributesArray.push(`${attributeKey}=${attributeValue}`);
      } else {
        // don't insert empty value if there is no value
        attributesArray.push(attributeKey);
      }

      return attributesArray
    }, []).join(';');

    // add expiration milliseconds onto the current milliseconds. Date() handles the carryover logic.
    const expirationDate = new Date();
    expirationDate.setTime(expirationDate.getTime() + expirationMilliseconds);

    document.cookie = `${cookieKey}=${cookieValue};expires=${expirationDate};${cookieAttributes}`;

    return true;
  }

  // ===============================================================================
  // Start of business logic

  // 24 hour timeout before resetting session cookie
  const cookieTimeoutInMilliseconds = 24 * 60 * 60 *  1000;
  // check every 10 seconds if the cookie has been cleared.
  const cookieCheckTime = 10 * 1000;

  // Boolean for checking if signifyd script has been imported
  let scriptTag = document.getElementById('sig-api');

  // set the session cookie if necessary with 24 hour timeout. This will be used by fraud team.
  // reset the cookie if a purchase occured
  let cookieValue = getCookie('FVSID');
  if (!cookieValue || data.purchase) {
    cookieValue = `${data.store_id}-${generateRandomGuid()}`;

    // set new cookie value and set new script attribute value
    setCookie('FVSID', cookieValue, cookieTimeoutInMilliseconds);
    // this will reset the cookie on purchase if the script already exists
    if (!!scriptTag) {
      scriptTag.setAttribute('data-order-session-id', cookieValue);
    }
  }

  // signifyd script has already been imported, return and don't create new script or setInterval
  if (!!scriptTag) {
    return;
  }

  // Import the signifyd script with expected attributes
  scriptTag = document.createElement('script');
  scriptTag.defer = true;
  scriptTag.type = 'text/javascript';
  scriptTag.id = 'sig-api';
  scriptTag.setAttribute('data-order-session-id', cookieValue);
  scriptTag.src = 'https://cdn-scripts.signifyd.com/api/script-tag.js';
  document.head.appendChild(scriptTag);

  // check every ten seconds and set cookie if missing (accounts for 24 hour timeout)
  setInterval(() => {
    const cookieExists = getCookie('FVSID');

    // only set a new cookie if timed out AND no cookie currently exists
    if (!cookieExists) {
      const newCookieId = `${data.store_id}-${generateRandomGuid()}`;

      // set new cookie value and set new script attribute value
      setCookie('FVSID', newCookieId, cookieTimeoutInMilliseconds);
      scriptTag.setAttribute('data-order-session-id', newCookieId);
    }
  }, cookieCheckTime);
};

<script async>window.wf_pixel_generic_commission_junction = data => {
  // check if call_name and enterprise_ids are missing
  if (!data.call_name || !data.enterprise_ids || !data.id) {
    return;
  }

  // return boolean value for argument
  const getBooleanArgumentValue = arg => {
    //boolean check
    if (arg === 'true' || arg === 'false') {
      return arg === 'true';
    }
    return arg;
  };

  // constants
  // argus pagealias to pageType mapping for CJ
  const pageAliasMapping = {
    'ProductPage': 'productDetail',
    'CheckoutReceipt': 'conversionConfirmation',
    'homepage': 'homepage',
    'SuperbrowseHotDeals': 'searchResults',
    'Superbrowse': 'searchResults',
    'Basket': 'cart',
    'Category': 'subCategory',
    'DepartmentCategory': 'department',
    'Keyword': 'searchResults',
    'DailyfairPDP': 'productDetail',
    'EventHome': 'homepage',
    'InspirationGallery': 'subCategory',
    'Gateway': 'accountSignup',
    'RegistryLanding': 'homepage',
    'Brand': 'department',
    'SolrEvent': 'searchResults',
    'Closeout': 'subCategory',
    'registry_application': 'accountCenter',
    'SearchOrders': 'accountCenter',
    'PicoMobileApplication': 'accountSignup',
    'Event': 'subCategory',
    'PicoApplication': 'accountSignup',
    'WayfairCard': 'accountCenter',
    'Help': 'accountCenter',
    'Clearance': 'subCategory',
    'Collection': 'subCategory',
    'OrderConfigurationPage': 'accountCenter',
    'BrowseByBrand': 'department'
  };

  /**
   * checks if all values in array are same length
   *
   * @return {Bool} true if values are same length
   */
  const areAllKeysSameLength = keys =>
    keys.reduce((length, key) => {
      if (length === false) {
        return length;
      }

      const valueLength =
        typeof data[key] === 'string' ? data[key].split(',').length : false;
      if ((length && length !== valueLength) || valueLength < 2) {
        return false;
      }
      return valueLength;
    }, 0);

  /**
   * creates a leaf object/array of objects to be added to the parent object
   *
   * @param {string} key parent key
   * @param {Array} keys array of keys
   * @param {object|undefined} defaultValue default value if provided
   *
   * @return {object|array} returns leaf object/array of objects
   */
  const setFields = (key, keys, defaultValue) => {
    const splittable = areAllKeysSameLength(keys);
    let returnObj = {...(defaultValue || {})};

    if (key === 'items' || (splittable && !defaultValue)) {
      keys.forEach(key => {
        if (typeof data[key] !== 'string') {
          data[key] = JSON.stringify(data[key]);
        }
        data[key] = data[key].split(',').map(el => el.trim());
      });
      returnObj = [];
    }

    keys.forEach(key => {
      let value = data[key];
      const currentKey = key.split('>').pop();

      if (Array.isArray(value)) {
        value.forEach((el, i) => {
          const currentValue = el;

          returnObj[i] = returnObj[i] || {};
          returnObj[i][currentKey] = currentValue;
        });
      } else {
        // if pageType, check for page alias mapping.
        if (currentKey === 'pageType') {
          // if there is no mapping, will return undefined
          value = pageAliasMapping[value];
        }

        if(value !== undefined) {
          returnObj[currentKey] = value;
        }
      }
    });

    return returnObj;
  };

  /**
   * returns the full nested data object when called with a list of original keys and level = 0
   * recurses through the original keys and creates a nested object with levels from keys split
   * by underscores
   *
   * @param {Array} originalKeys array of original keys (strings)
   * @param {number} level current level in object
   *
   * @return {object} returns child object or object based on level
   */
  const getDataObject = (originalKeys, level) => {
    const returnObj = {};
    const {recurses, leaves, defaults} = originalKeys
      .map(key => ({
        splitKeys: key.split('>'),
        originalKey: key,
      }))
      .reduce(
        (result, {splitKeys, originalKey}) => {
          const currentKey = splitKeys[level];

          // If the level has more than 2, it means that this is not a leaf object
          // levels start at 0 and split keys will always have a minimum of length 2
          if (splitKeys.length - level > 2) {
            result.defaults[currentKey] = result.defaults[currentKey] || {};

            result.recurses[currentKey] = result.recurses[currentKey] || {
              keys: [],
              level: level + 1,
            };
            result.recurses[currentKey].keys.push(originalKey);
          } else {
            result.leaves[currentKey] = result.leaves[currentKey] || [];
            result.leaves[currentKey].push(originalKey);
          }
          return result;
        },
        {
          // parameters for recursive calls stored here
          recurses: {},
          // keys for leaf objects in the nested object stored here
          leaves: {},
          // default values for keys when applicable stored here
          defaults: {},
        }
      );

    // this creates an object with all the values from
    // keys and sets it to the relevant current key
    Object.keys(leaves).forEach(
      key => (returnObj[key] = setFields(key, leaves[key], defaults[key]))
    );

    // This uses recursive calls to create nested object
    Object.keys(recurses).forEach(key => {
      const {keys, level} = recurses[key];
      returnObj[key] = {
        ...(returnObj[key] || {}),
        ...getDataObject(keys, level),
      };
    });

    return returnObj;
  };

  /**
   * gets call parameters from data
   *
   * @param {string} prefix starting phrase used to fetch objects
   *
   * @return {object} object containing all Commission Junction data
   */
  const getCallObjects = prefix => {
    const dataObject = getDataObject(
      Object.keys(data).filter(el => el.indexOf(prefix) === 0),
      0
    );

    const callObjects = Object.keys(dataObject)
      .sort()
      .map(key => dataObject[key]);

    return callObjects;
  };

  /**
   * calculate net prices for items when vatDivisionFactor defined
   * 
   * @param {Array} items array of items added in cart
   * @param {number} vatDivisionFactor vat factor for a store
   *
   * @return array of items with netUnitPrices
   */
  const getItemNetPrices = (items, vatDivisionFactor) => {
    if(vatDivisionFactor && items && items.length>0) {
      items.forEach((item)=>{
          item.unitPrice = (item.unitPrice/vatDivisionFactor).toFixed(2);
      });
    };
    return items;
  }

  /**
 * Parses the purchase item details string from the `purchase_details` parameter.
 * This string contains multiple items, each with an item ID, quantity, and amount,
 * formatted as "ITEM1=ID&QTY1=quantity&AMT1=amount&ITEM2=ID&QTY2=quantity&AMT2=amount...".

 * `itemId`, `quantity`, and `unitPrice` properties.
 *
 * @param {string} purchase_details - A query string formatted string containing item details.
 *                                           Example format: "ITEM1=A000314007&QTY1=1&AMT1=102.6&ITEM2=A000881624&QTY2=1&AMT2=26.99..."
 * @return {Array} An array of objects where each object represents an item with the following properties:
